        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="9sBdW33pM4JB0q4Lbeby-10" value="&lt;h1 data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Client requirements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1 data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;GUI interface to configure multiple port@server licenses with different lmutil/lmgrd paths&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Start/Stop/Reread functions&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;check, edit &amp;amp; update option file, through text editor first but needs to be upgradable to a GUI for syntax checking &amp;amp; highlighting in the future&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;First verion is in Python but needs to be in Java in the future&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Able to communicate with Server through TCP/UDP, the server port is predefined in a config file, while the client port is random in a given range (from low to high, use the first available one)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Able to get stdout/stderr of the client, contineously parse the new lines and send to server to digest&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Able to run lmstat on each port@server, parse it to be a structral table and send the samples to server to digest (interval is configurable)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Able to specify the log file path. Log can rotate automatically for a new license file start&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Able to show features&#39; count and expiry information on the main form, with highlighting (expired, close to expire) critical features&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Able to run in background when the GUI is closed (let user choose to quit or run on background)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;when a gui starts, it will connect to the background one if exists&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Cross-platform (To support both Linux and Windows). should start with Linux first but can be easily extended to Windows (with plugin or something else)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="700" y="70" width="460" height="590" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="9sBdW33pM4JB0q4Lbeby-11" value="&lt;h1 data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Server requirements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1 data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;GUI interface&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;able to store the configuration of clients that ever connected&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;Configuration for each client is versioned&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;Able to see the status of each clients&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;Able to control each client through GUI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;* upload / update license.dat file&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;* check the heath of the service&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;* start/stop/reread&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;ingest the data received from clients, put them into a postgresql database&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;written in Python, but the whole server binary (including postgresql) need to be packaged into one single release portable folder so that can be easily installed in a Linux server&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="60" y="460" width="440" height="360" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="9sBdW33pM4JB0q4Lbeby-13" value="lmgrd simulator" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="600" y="690" width="120" height="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="9sBdW33pM4JB0q4Lbeby-14" value="lmstat simulator" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="600" y="860" width="120" height="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="9sBdW33pM4JB0q4Lbeby-15" value="&lt;h1 data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;lmgrd simulator requirements&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;div data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;miic the way lmgrd works, &#39;lmgrd -c license.data -o license.log.20260126&#39;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;take dummy license.data file with dummy features&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;when it&#39;s running, it can take license request and book keeping the usage&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;it only supports floating license for now&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;it supports option file&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="760" y="650" width="430" height="120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="9sBdW33pM4JB0q4Lbeby-16" value="&lt;h1 data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;lmstat simulator requirements&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;div data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;mimic the way lmstat works, &#39;lmstat -c port@server -a -i&#39; or &#39;lmstat -c port@server -f feature_name -i&#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;can be called peroidically to generate license usage samples&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-imt_insert_failed=&quot;1&quot;&gt;the output is to stdout, error to stderr&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="750" y="820" width="430" height="120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
